President Joseph R. Biden, Jr. will award the Medal of Honor to four U.S. Army Soldiers who fought in the Vietnam War: Staff Sergeant Edward N. Kaneshiro (posthumous), Specialist Five Dwight W. Birdwell, Specialist Five Dennis M. Fujii, and retired Major John J. Duffy. Staff Sergeant Kaneshiro will receive the Medal of Honor posthumously for acts of gallantry and intrepidity above and beyond the call of duty while serving as an infantry squad leader. Specialist Five Birdwell will receive the Medal of Honor for his actions during an enemy assault on an airbase. Specialist Five Fujii will receive the Medal of Honor for his bravery during a mission to evacuate wounded personnel. Major Duffy will receive the Medal of Honor for his actions as a senior advisor to the 11th Airborne Battalion. The Medal of Honor is awarded to members of the armed forces who distinguish themselves conspicuously by gallantry and intrepidity at the risk of their own lives above and beyond the call of duty.